HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 670
By Todd
A RESOLUTION to honor Bobbie Patray for her many years of
service to Eagle Forum and leadership in the
State of Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
recognize and honor individuals who have given selflessly of their time, talents, and convictions
to preserve and promote the foundational values that strengthen our families, communities, and
nation; and
WHEREAS, Bobbie Patray has devoted an extraordinary fifty years to the mission and
work of Eagle Forum, faithfully advancing its vision by educating and informing citizens, offering
insight into the legislative process, and encouraging principled engagement in public life; and
WHEREAS, for the past thirty-eight years, she has served as the president of the
Tennessee Eagle Forum, becoming a trusted advocate, mentor, and leader whose influence
has reached far beyond the statehouse to touch the lives of countless Tennesseans; and
WHEREAS, Bobbie Patray's passion for equipping future leaders is especially evident in
her tireless investment in Teen Eagles and her weekly interns, providing them with wisdom and
encouragement and instilling in them a deep love for both country and truthâ€”reflecting her
sincere devotion to young people of all ages; and
WHEREAS, her leadership has not only shaped public discourse and policy, but has
also empowered generations of Tennesseans to be thoughtful, courageous, and informed
participants in the democratic process; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Patray's legacy is one marked by steadfast faith, moral clarity, and
servant-hearted tenacity; she has served as a beacon of hope and conviction for both
Tennessee and the nation at large; and
